            <h2>How to Choose the Right University Programme for Your Career Goals</h2>
            <p>Choosing the right university programme is crucial for aligning your education with your career goals. Start by identifying your interests and strengths.</p>
               <p> Consider what subjects you enjoy and excel in, as well as any relevant extracurricular activities. </p>
               <p> Research potential career paths and the academic programmes that support them. </p>
               <p> Look into the job market demand, growth prospects, and average salaries in your field of interest. Consult with career advisors, teachers, and professionals in the industry for insights and guidance. </p>
               <p> Additionally, consider the curriculum and specializations offered by different universities to ensure they match your career aspirations. </p>
               <p> Making an informed decision will set you on a path toward a fulfilling and successful career.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="modal2" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="close" data-modal="modal2">&times;</span>
            <h2>What to Do if You’re Undecided About Your Major</h2>
            <p>If you’re undecided about your major, don’t worry—many students are in the same boat. Start by exploring your interests and taking a variety of courses in your first year to see what excites you. Meet with academic advisors to discuss your options and potential career paths. 
                <br>Consider taking career assessment tests to identify your strengths and interests. Participate in extracurricular activities and internships to gain practical experience and insights into different fields. Don’t rush your decision; it's okay to take your time to find the right fit. 
                <br>Remember, choosing a major is a significant decision, but it’s not set in stone—many students change their majors as they discover new interests and opportunities.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="modal3" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="close" data-modal="modal3">&times;</span>
            <h2>Exploring Interdisciplinary Studies: Pros and Cons</h2>
            <p>Interdisciplinary studies offer a unique educational approach by integrating multiple fields of study. One major advantage is the ability to gain a broader perspective and versatile skill set, which can be highly valuable in the job market. 
                <br>It fosters critical thinking, creativity, and problem-solving by encouraging students to make connections between diverse disciplines. However, there are also challenges. Interdisciplinary programmes may lack the depth of specialized single-discipline programmes, potentially making it harder to master a specific field. 
                <br>Additionally, finding a cohesive programme that meets your interests and career goals can be difficult. 
                <br>Ultimately, interdisciplinary studies are ideal for students who are curious, adaptable, and interested in combining different academic areas to create a unique educational experience.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="modal4" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="close" data-modal="modal4">&times;</span>
            <h2>How to Write a Winning Personal Statement for University Applications</h2>
            <p>A winning personal statement is your chance to showcase your personality, achievements, and aspirations to the admissions committee. 
                <br> Start by reflecting on your experiences and what makes you a unique candidate.
                <br> Be honest and personal, sharing stories that highlight your strengths and passions. 
                <br>Structure your statement with a clear introduction, body, and conclusion. 
                <br>The introduction should grab the reader’s attention, while the body should provide detailed examples of your achievements and experiences. 
                <br>Use specific, concrete examples to illustrate your points. 
                <br>Conclude by summarizing your goals and why you’re excited about the programme. Proofread your statement multiple times to ensure it’s free of errors. 
                <br> A well-crafted personal statement can make a significant difference in your application.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="modal5" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="close" data-modal="modal5">&times;</span>
            <h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid in Your University Application</h2>
            <p>When applying to university, avoiding common mistakes can greatly improve your chances of success. First, carefully read and follow all application instructions. Missing deadlines or submitting incomplete applications are critical errors. 
                <br> Ensure that your personal statement is well-written and free of grammatical errors. 
                <br> Avoid generic statements; instead, tailor your application to each university and programme. Proofread all materials meticulously. Seek feedback from teachers or mentors to improve your application. 
                <br> Additionally, don’t underestimate the importance of extracurricular activities; highlight your involvement and achievements. 
                <br> Finally, be honest and authentic in your application. Universities value genuine passion and commitment. 
                <br> By avoiding these common mistakes, you can present a strong and compelling application.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="modal6" class="modal">
