            <h2>How to Ace Your University Admissions Interview</h2>
            <p>Acing your university admissions interview requires preparation and confidence. Start by researching the university and programme to understand what they value in applicants. 
                <br> Practice common interview questions and develop thoughtful, articulate responses. Highlight your strengths, achievements, and experiences that align with the programme’s goals. 
                <br> Prepare questions to ask the interviewer to demonstrate your genuine interest. Dress professionally and arrive on time. During the interview, be confident, maintain good eye contact, and listen carefully. 
                <br> Show enthusiasm for the programme and explain how it aligns with your career goals. Follow up with a thank-you email to express your appreciation. 
                <br> With preparation and a positive attitude, you can make a strong impression during your admissions interview.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

