            <h2>Tips for Building a Strong Relationship with Your Roommate</h2>
            <p>Building a strong relationship with your roommate can enhance your university experience. 
                <br> Start by communicating openly and setting clear boundaries and expectations regarding cleanliness, noise, and shared responsibilities. 
                <br> Respect each other’s space and privacy. 
                <br> Find common interests and spend time together to build a bond, but also ensure you give each other space. 
                <br> Address any conflicts directly and calmly, aiming for a compromise. 
                <br> Establishing a mutual understanding and respect from the beginning can prevent misunderstandings and foster a positive living environment. 
                <br> Remember, a good roommate relationship is built on communication, respect, and compromise.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="modal9" class="modal">
