            <h2>Creating a Balanced Schedule: Academics, Social Life, and Self-Care</h2>
            <p>Creating a balanced schedule is essential for success and well-being in university. Start by prioritizing your academic responsibilities, such as classes, assignments, and study time. 
                <br> Use a planner or digital calendar to organize your commitments. 
                <br> Schedule regular breaks and downtime to avoid burnout. Incorporate social activities and time with friends to maintain a healthy social life. 
                <br> Don’t forget to allocate time for self-care, including exercise, healthy eating, and sufficient sleep. 
                <br> Regularly review and adjust your schedule to maintain balance. 
                <br> By managing your time effectively, you can achieve academic success while enjoying a fulfilling university experience.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="modal10" class="modal">
