            <h2>Top Apps and Tools Every University Student Should Use</h2>
            <p>Leveraging the right apps and tools can significantly enhance your university experience. For note-taking and organization, consider Evernote or OneNote. 
                <br> Google Drive and Dropbox are excellent for cloud storage and collaboration. 
                <br> Grammarly helps improve your writing, while Zotero aids in managing research and citations. 
                <br> For time management, use apps like Todoist or Trello to keep track of tasks and deadlines. 
                <br> Quizlet is great for studying and creating flashcards. 
                <br> Additionally, Microsoft Teams or Zoom can facilitate virtual meetings and group work. 
                <br> Utilizing these apps and tools can help you stay organized, productive, and efficient throughout your university journey.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

