            <h2>How to Stay Safe Online: Cybersecurity Tips for Students</h2>
            <p>Staying safe online is crucial for university students. Start by using strong, unique passwords for each account and enabling two-factor authentication. 
                <br> Be cautious of phishing emails and suspicious links, and avoid sharing personal information online. 
                <br> Regularly update your software and use reputable antivirus programs to protect against malware. 
                <br> Use secure, encrypted connections, especially when accessing sensitive information. Be mindful of your digital footprint and privacy settings on social media. 
                <br> Educate yourself about common online threats and how to avoid them. 
                <br> By following these cybersecurity tips, you can protect your personal information and stay safe online.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>





